pected, concentration, problem solving, responsibility. Weaknesses: arrogant, weak leadership. Leadership weak could affect crew. Arrogance may affect teamwork.\n\nWe need provisional preference. Which candidate balances strengths and weaknesses best? Likely B or C. B has stress handling, conscientiousness, weather assessment (critical for long flights). Weaknesses are attitude but maybe manageable. C is reliable and good crew atmosphere, quick decisions, but communication difficulty and egocentric may hinder teamwork. Also not willing to further education, which may be a problem for long-term suitability.\n\nThus B seems strong overall, with technical competence and stress handling, though attitude issues. D has strong problem solving and responsibility but weak leadership and arrogance.\n\nA has good anticipation and leadership but unorganized and poor criticism handling.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate B.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: we lack info on reliability of A, B, D; we don't know actual teamwork performance beyond what's given. Also unknown about long-term development for B.\n\nWe can ask other agents for missing strengths: e.g., reliability of B, D, A; leadership of B; communication skills of B; etc. But we need to produce public message now.\n\nWe must include evidence from others? None yet. So just our own.\n\nProvide METADATA vote B.\n\nProceed."}
